    <string name="terms_of_service">Terms of service</string>
    <string name="tos_content"><h5> Privacy policy </h5> <br /> <p> LeafFeed stores feeds, articles, account credentials, and preferences locally on your device. LeafFeed does not operate an analytics or advertising service. </p> <br /> <p> When you enable synchronization, feed data is sent to the service you configure. When you use an AI feature, the requested titles or article content is sent directly to the OpenAI-compatible service URL you configure. Review that provider\'s privacy policy before enabling it. </p> <br /> <p> LeafFeed requires network access to retrieve feeds and online content, and may use background work for synchronization and notifications. </p> <br /> <h5> Disclaimers </h5> <br /> <p> LeafFeed is a content collection and reading tool. You are responsible for the feeds, services, and content you configure and use. </p> <br /> <h5> Open source license </h5> <br /> <p> LeafFeed is free and open-source software under the GNU GPL 3.0. The source code and license are available at the project repository. </p> <br /> <p> - https://github.com/conice/LeafFeed </p> <p> - https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html </p></string>
